summary:
There is no evidence indicating that lucatumumab binds to CD140; it does not appear in any database records related to targeted therapies involving specific antigen-receptor pairs including those targeting CD140. This conclusion stems directly from an exhaustive search showing lacation of the drug’s target profile across known mAbs, confirming its non-involvement in CD140-related pathways.

