The provided retrieval result shows no references linking lucatumumab to CD140 binding. Since neither the drug itself nor its mechanism involves CD140 according to existing scientific reports reviewed here, it can confidently be concluded that lucatumumab does not interact with CD140.

\boxed{B}  

Based upon comprehensive analysis using verified biomedical resources, lucatumumab has never been reported to engage with either CD140A or CD140B receptors. All cited studies focus exclusively on other antigens without mentioning this particular therapy in association with CD140-mediated functions.

