Only one source mentions “lucatumumab” briefly but states it acts via inhibition of CXCL12/CXCR4 axis—not linked to CD140—and thus indirectly suggests alternative pathway involvement rather than engagement with CD140. However even then, no functional cross-talk was described implying potential binding affinity toward CD140 proteins specifically. Hence overall still insufficient grounds exist for affirming direct binding activity against CD140.

