Despite multiple iterations refining our query scope through additional tools calls and contextual filtering based on established immunotherapies' profiles—including extensive coverage around common targets like PD-L1, HER2, B-cell markers—we find absolutely nothing connecting luca-tumab with expression patterns associated with endogenous ligands recognized by CD140 isoforms. Consequently, while certain classes may share overlapping roles during inflammatory responses due to shared tissue distribution features, actual molecular recognition remains unproven under standard assay conditions defined in published research protocols regarding recombinant protein–antibody assays used clinically validated platforms worldwide today.

